<div class="flex gap-8">
  <%= render "docs/sidebar", current_page: "devices" %>

  <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">💻 Devices</h1>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500">Devices are endpoints (laptops, phones, servers) linked to ZTLP Users.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What is a Device?</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">
        A Device is a <strong class="text-gray-900">registered endpoint</strong> on the ZTLP network. Every device
        belongs to a ZTLP User and gets its own cryptographic identity — separate from the user's.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        A single user can have multiple devices, each independently authenticated.
        If one device is compromised, revoke it without affecting the others.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Device Types</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-3">
        <% [
          ["💻", "Laptop", "Portable workstations"],
          ["🖥️", "Desktop", "Fixed workstations"],
          ["🖧", "Server", "Service endpoints"],
          ["📱", "Mobile", "Phones and tablets"],
          ["📡", "IoT", "Sensors, edge devices"]
        ].each do |icon, label, desc| %>
          <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-3 text-center">
            <span class="text-2xl"><%= icon %></span>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 mt-1"><%= label %></div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500"><%= desc %></p>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Key Provisioning</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">When a device is created, Bootstrap generates a real Ed25519 key pair:</p>
      <ol class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-ztlp-100 text-ztlp-700 text-xs font-bold flex-shrink-0">1</span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-900">Key Generation:</strong> Ed25519 key pair via OpenSSL. Raw 32-byte keys extracted from DER.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-ztlp-100 text-ztlp-700 text-xs font-bold flex-shrink-0">2</span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-900">Public Key:</strong> Stored Base64 in DB, written to device config, registered with NS.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-ztlp-100 text-ztlp-700 text-xs font-bold flex-shrink-0">3</span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-900">Private Key:</strong> Encrypted with AES-256-GCM using key derived from enrollment secret. Stored as Base64(IV + AuthTag + Ciphertext).</span>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Enrollment Methods</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ztlp-600 mb-1">🎫 Token Enrollment</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Admin generates a token, user runs <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">ztlp setup --token &lt;TOKEN&gt;</code>. See <%= link_to "Enrollment", doc_page_path(page: "enrollment"), class: "text-ztlp-600 hover:underline" %> docs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ztlp-600 mb-1">🔑 IdP Enrollment (SSO)</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Connect Google Workspace, Okta, or other OIDC providers. Users authenticate with their corporate credentials and devices are auto-provisioned.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ztlp-600 mb-1">📋 Manual</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Admin creates a device in the UI, downloads the config, and manually installs it on the endpoint.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Device Lifecycle</h2>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm mb-4">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-green-100 text-green-800">Enrolled</span>
        <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-red-100 text-red-800">Revoked</span>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-xs text-gray-500">
        <p><strong class="text-green-700">Enrolled:</strong> Device is active and can authenticate on the ZTLP network.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-red-700">Revoked:</strong> Device is permanently disabled. A revocation record is published to NS.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "docs/prev_next", current_page: "devices" %>
  </div>
</div>
